class Admin(commands.Cog):
    def cog_check(self, ctx: commands.Context):
        if not ctx.guild:
            raise commands.NoPrivateMessage('This command can\'t be used in DM channels.')
        return True

    async def cog_command_error(self, ctx: commands.Context, error: commands.CommandError):
        await ctx.send('An error occurred: {}'.format(str(error)))

    @commands.command(name='HasPerms', aliases=['hasperms'])
    @commands.has_permissions(administrator=True)
    async def _HasPerms(self, ctx: commands.Context, input : str = "administrator", input2 : str = "", input3 : str = ""):

        if (input2 != ""):
            input2 = "_" + input2
        if (input3 != ""):
            input3 = "_" + input3

        input = (input + input2 + input3).lower() 

        """lists all roles with that permission"""
        global Role_Perms
        i = "Here are all roles that have the permission: `" + input + "`\n" 

        if not input in Role_Perms:
            return await ctx.send("Paramater was not part of role permissions.\n- if you would like to see all role permissions, use the command `ListPerms`")

        roles = [r for r in ctx.guild.roles if any(p[1] and p[0] == input for p in r.permissions)]

        if (roles.count == 0):
            return await ctx.send("no roles were found with this permission.")

        for role in roles:
             i += "- " + str(role.name).replace('@', '') + "\n"
        
        await ctx.send(i)```
